## Details

When an object is coming from `req.body` or `req.query`, coming from the express framework. The value of this property can be controlled by the user. This could be abused by an attacker to craft the properties of the object to crash the application or bypass its logic. As such, consider checking the type of the object.

If this weakness is present, illegitimate input provided from the user's end could lead to unpredictable results such as the program crashing, unauthorized access to secure resources or command execution at the server side. In addition, if the server is overwhelmed by these types of malfunctions, it may lead to denial of service to legitimate users and tasks.

Example:

```
module.exports = function(req, res) {
    var data = req.query;
      // type of value isnt checked before being used
      data.ids = data.ids.split(',');
      doStuff(data.ids);

  };
```



## Best practices for prevention
* Adopt a zero-trust model in which all input is considered potentially suspect.
* Check the type of the object.

Example:

```
module.exports = function(req, res) {
    var data = req.query;
    if (data.ids && typeof data.ids == 'string') {

      // type of value is checked
      data.ids = data.ids.split(',');
      doStuff(data.ids);
    } else {}
  };
```

